title: Cindy O'Laughlin
added: In 2020, O’Laughlin sponsored legislation to require Missouri athletes to compete in gender-specific sports with the gender they were born with. <ref>https://www.kmov.com/news/missouri-senator-proposes-trans-student-athletes-to-play-sports-on-gender-identified-at-birth/article_09a8ff2e-36df-11ea-bd91-4fb6daa856cb.html</ref>

title: Cindy O'Laughlin
added: O’Laughlin has been a member of various civic organizations such as the Shelby County Chamber of Commerce & Industry and the Shelby County Economic Development Board. She has also served on numerous statewide boards such as the Associated Builders and Contractors and the Missouri Club for Growth.

In October 2017, O’Laughlin announced her candidacy for state senate. Touting her experience in the private sector, O’Laughlin ran as an outsider that wanted to run the state like a business. <ref>https://www.whig.com/20171010/olaughlin-enters-missouri-senate-race/</ref>
